97.8	Pirates_of_Silicon_Valley	Pirates of Silicon Valley	Pirates of Silicon Valley is a 1999 made-for-television film directed by Martyn Burke and based on the book Fire in the Valley: The Making of The Personal Computer by Paul Freiberger and Michael Swaine. The film documents the impact on the development of the personal computer of the rivalry between Apple Computer and Microsoft. It spans the time period of the early 1970s to 1997, when Steve Jobs and Bill Gates (Anthony Michael Hall) develop a partnership after Jobs returns to Apple Computer.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/30/Movieposterposv.jpg/220px-Movieposterposv.jpg
